highlights: Close proximity to I-24 . Good traffic flow. Recently updated access drive . Well maintained with a new roof in 2018.
propOverview:
This property is well-suited for warehousing space.  The entire building length is 500 feet with the width being 110 feet. The interior firewall/ heat sensor controlled door openings are 7'6" wide x 9' 6" high, there are also firewalls separating each bay.  The building has multiple cameras on the interior and exterior, sensors and locks for security . A dry sprinkler system is also located within the building. 
The interior is well lit and has multiple LED lights in each bay. 
The building is not climate controlled. It does have good ventilation around the roof perimeter plus rood vents. 
The bays themselves are 45 feet deep x 16' 6" wide. the forklift aisle path is 17 feet wide. Aisles are coated with an epoxy system with skid-proofing near dock door. The dock has a hydraulic leveler and locking system. 
The are multiple entry points including ground-level sliding doors and two walk-through doors. 
The roof was updated in 2018 and it has insulation under the TPO/rubber roof. 
Property is located near Ft. Campbell Blvd at the intersection of 24th Street and S. Virginia. It is 30 minutes from Clarksville and
 1 hour+ from Nashville. Only minutes to I-24/PennyrileParkway/I-69 . There is ample space to turn in off of S. Virginia and loading/unloading. 
Owners would consider material handling services if required by Tenant.

propOverview:
8341 Beechcraft Avenue is a 35,477 square foot, industrial building which was originally constructed in 1998. The property is situated on a 2.64 acre parcel, located in Montgomery County, MD. The property, which has been well maintained, consists of two stories and is divided into three sections. The section located in the front of the building and on the 2nd story (mezzanine) is comprised of 6,450 sf of fully built out office space with common bathrooms and a common kitchenette area. The section located in the middle of the building and on the first floor offers 17,740 sf of fully built out commercial kitchen space equipped four separate kitchen spaces, new appliances, multiple freezers and fridges for storage, break room and washing areas. The section on grade in the rear of the property contains 11,288 sf of warehouse space with 22’ clear heights, full sprinkler system, four loading docks and one drive in bay.
The property is located in the Montgomery County Airpark area of Gaithersburg, MD. The region is known for the Airpark that services the direct area. Surrounding the Airpark is a large supply of industrial and flex properties that make up a majority of the commercial corridor. The Airpark and commercial corridor are surrounded by numerous densely settled residential communities. The property benefits from its access to many major highways and thoroughfares. It is conveniently located just off the heavily traveled routes 124, 115 and 355 which filter into major highways – I-270, I-370 and the Inter County Connector (ICC). Washington DC is located just 20 miles from the site. The property is zoned I-L, or Light Industrial. Gaithersburg contains a population of 68,710 within the Montgomery County Population of 1.059 million.
